<section class="py-6 bg-base-200">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold mb-4 text-center">How StyloBot Detects Bots</h2>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
            <div class="bg-base-100 rounded-lg p-4">
                <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
                    <i class="bx bx-globe text-lg hero-accent-text"></i>
                    <h3 class="font-bold text-sm hero-accent-text">Browser Analysis</h3>
                </div>
                <p class="text-xs text-base-content/60">User-agent parsing, version age checking, and inconsistency detection between claimed and actual browser capabilities.</p>
                <a href="https://github.com/scottgal/stylobot/tree/main/docs/user-agent-detection.md" target="_blank" class="text-[10px] mt-1 inline-block hero-accent-text">Learn more</a>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-base-100 rounded-lg p-4">
                <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
                    <i class="bx bx-fingerprint text-lg hero-accent-alt"></i>
                    <h3 class="font-bold text-sm hero-accent-alt">Fingerprinting</h3>
                </div>
                <p class="text-xs text-base-content/60">TLS (JA3/JA4), TCP/IP (p0f), HTTP/2 (AKAMAI), and client-side browser fingerprints create a unique signature for each visitor.</p>
                <a href="https://github.com/scottgal/stylobot/tree/main/docs/tls-fingerprinting.md" target="_blank" class="text-[10px] mt-1 inline-block hero-accent-alt">Learn more</a>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-base-100 rounded-lg p-4">
                <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
                    <i class="bx bx-pulse text-lg signal-positive"></i>
                    <h3 class="font-bold text-sm signal-positive">Behavioral Analysis</h3>
                </div>
                <p class="text-xs text-base-content/60">Request timing, waveform analysis, and browsing patterns distinguish natural human behavior from automated scripts.</p>
                <a href="https://github.com/scottgal/stylobot/tree/main/docs/behavioral-detection.md" target="_blank" class="text-[10px] mt-1 inline-block signal-positive">Learn more</a>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-base-100 rounded-lg p-4">
                <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
                    <i class="bx bx-cloud text-lg signal-warning"></i>
                    <h3 class="font-bold text-sm signal-warning">Network Intelligence</h3>
                </div>
                <p class="text-xs text-base-content/60">IP reputation, datacenter detection, header analysis, and security tool identification reveal the true source of traffic.</p>
                <a href="https://github.com/scottgal/stylobot/tree/main/docs/ip-detection.md" target="_blank" class="text-[10px] mt-1 inline-block signal-warning">Learn more</a>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-base-100 rounded-lg p-4">
                <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
                    <i class="bx bx-brain text-lg signal-danger"></i>
                    <h3 class="font-bold text-sm signal-danger">AI Classification</h3>
                </div>
                <p class="text-xs text-base-content/60">Heuristic AI model runs on every request. Optional LLM escalation via Ollama provides natural-language explanations for complex cases.</p>
                <a href="https://github.com/scottgal/stylobot/tree/main/docs/ai-detection.md" target="_blank" class="text-[10px] mt-1 inline-block signal-danger">Learn more</a>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-base-100 rounded-lg p-4">
                <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
                    <i class="bx bx-shield text-lg signal-muted"></i>
                    <h3 class="font-bold text-sm signal-muted">Action Policies</h3>
                </div>
                <p class="text-xs text-base-content/60">You decide what happens: allow, throttle silently, challenge with CAPTCHA, block outright, or redirect to a honeypot. Detection is separate from response.</p>
